# Repo Standards

## Stack
* Database: PostgreSQL
* Backend: Spring Boot, Maven, Lombok, Logback SLF4J, Micrometer Tracing Bridge OTel
* Frontend: React Native
* Local deployment: Docker compose
* AWS deployment: GitHub Actions, Terraform, EKS Fargate, Amplify Hosting, RDS PostgreSQL, CloudWatch Logs

## Base project structure: monorepo/
  * .github/workflows
    * deploy-backend.yml
    * deploy-frontend.yml
    * deploy-infra.yml
  * backend/
    * k8s/
    * src/
    * .dockerignore
    * Dockerfile
    * pom.xml
  * frontend/
  * infra/
  * docker-compose.yml
  * README.md

  
## Simulation of real financial sector features
## Variables: single-source-of-truth variables: no redundant values
  * GitHub Actions variables and secrets: developer-chosen inputs used by GitHub Workflows
  * AWS SSM Parameter Store: outputs from Infra GitHub Workflow used by other GitHub Workflows. SSM_PARAM_PREFIX as explicit prefix
  * default spring boot properties for local deployment
## frontend
  * create frontend/package-lock.json before CD pipelines: cd frontend && docker run --rm -v "$PWD:/app" -w /app node:20-alpine npm install
## backend
  * Use java records where possible
  * application.yml
    * default values for developing environment
    * production-environment-first: development environment with single env var specifying the local profile, additional application-local.yml
    * lombok: @Value and @Qualifier as copyable annotations.
    * jackson.deserialization.fail-on-unknown-properties: false
  * NFR
    * Usability: HATEOAS API
    * Maintainability and testability:
      * Screaming? Architecture with Clean Architecture
        ```
        src/main/
        |-- java/com/example/myproject/
