        ``` 
      * observability
        * pod CPU/memory metrics
        * log entry with
          * timestamp
          * level
          * service_name
          * thread_name
          * traceId 
          * logger_name
          * message
          * structuredArguments: LogPayload with URL and body, response status and body, duration
          * stackTrace
        * logaback with JSON encoder, LogRepository with SLF4J and LogPayload
        * logging in Controllers, RestControllerAdvice, external services requests
    * Portability: docker containers
    * Availability: scalability / resilience / reliability
      * RestControllerAdvice
      * custom ApiException with status and a contructor with cause Throwable
      * ErrorResponse with status, message, errors
      * fargate multi-az
      * k8s liveness/readiness probes
      * Performance
        * no stack trace in info logs
        * OncePerRequestFilter with @Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE)
        * close no longer needed Closeable resources
        * pagination
    * security
      * AWS Secrets Manager SDK for reading secrets from the backend
      * eks-pod-identity for authorization to AWS resources
      * user credentials on request headers, not on body which is logged
      * BOLA-proof
        * UUIDs as db records id

## Production
* vpc.tf
  * single_nat_gateway = false and set one_nat_gateway_per_az = true
